[SN]TITLE[SN]
James Hanson: Sheffield United set to sign Bradford City striker

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Sheffield United are set to sign Bradford City striker James Hanson for an undisclosed fee.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
BBC Sport understands the Blades are hopeful of completing a deal on Monday for the 29-year-old, who is out of contract at the end of the season.
Hanson joined Bradford from non-league Guiseley in July 2009 and scored 77 goals in 281 league appearances.
He helped the Bantams reach the League Cup final and win promotion from League Two in 2013.
